Definition: lacking a sense of security or affording no ease or reassurance
Example: farmers were uneasy until rain finally came; uneasy about his health; gave an uneasy laugh; uneasy lies the head that wears the crown; an uneasy coalition government; an uneasy calm; an uneasy silence fell on the group
Synonyms: noun, feeling, uneasiness, EASY, TENSE, UNCOMFORTABLE, UNQUIET, lacking, a, sense, of, security, or, affording, no, ease, reassurance, farmers, were, uneasy, until, rain, finally, came, about, his, health, gave, an, laugh, lies, the, head, that, wears, crown, coalition, government, calm, silence, fell, on, group
Category: adj.all
